```json
{
  "application": "Cormorant",
  "software_requirements": [
    "gcc/8.1.0",
    "cuda/10.0",
    "miniconda3",
    "Cormorant"
  ],
  "resource_requirements": {
    "time": "24 hours",
    "memory": "20GB",
    "partition": "rondror",
    "gpu": "1",
    "gpu_memory": "12GB",
    "email": "mvoegele@stanford.edu",
    "dependency": "singleton",
    "job_name": "lba-id30-cutoff-CUTOFF-maxnumat-MAXNUM-cormorant"
  }
}
```

This script is running a machine learning model called **Cormorant**. The script specifies a number of software and resource requirements.

**Software Requirements:**

- **gcc/8.1.0**: This indicates a specific version of the GCC compiler is required.
- **cuda/10.0**: This is the CUDA toolkit, necessary for using GPUs for accelerated computation.
- **miniconda3**:  A lightweight Python distribution used to manage dependencies.
- **Cormorant**:  The machine learning model itself.

**Resource Requirements:**

- **Time**: The script is allocated 24 hours of runtime.
- **Memory**:  The script requires 20GB of RAM.
- **Partition**: It needs to be run on the "rondror" cluster partition.
- **GPU**: It requires access to one GPU.
- **GPU Memory**: The GPU needs to have at least 12GB of memory.
- **Email**: The user will be notified by email when the job ends or fails.
- **Dependency**: The job requires a "singleton" dependency, which means it can only run if no other jobs with the same dependency are running.
- **Job Name**: The job is labeled with the name "lba-id30-cutoff-CUTOFF-maxnumat-MAXNUM-cormorant".
